name: Studies in Structure [TIN017]
description: This is the third full-length album from Longitudinal Expanse and shows the collective continuing in the abstract/experimental direction of last April's "Pharmacy." "Studies in Structure" draws on material from several years but focuses on recordings from 2013. This collection of improvised recordings shows musicians searching for bliss in layers of loops, effects, drones, and noise in a live, unpredictable setting. You can stream the album in its entirety now on the Longitudinal Expanse bandcamp! Cassettes go on sale on January 7th. Side A: Existential Threat 5938 ORD Drone Decay Someday We'll Land (~24 mins.) Side B: Downward Spiral Intermission from Another Planet Psychedelic Passage "Ether" jam (~22 mins.) For full liner notes, please see the album's Bandcamp page.

name: c r i s i s/s l e e p e r [TIN016]
description: "c r i s i s/s l e e p e r" is the first release from electronic/ambient project Shortwaves. Loops, samples, and synthesized drones are all beautifully arranged to create soundscapes that are always subtly changing; moving the listener through both serene and desolate moments. Stream an excerpt of this release on our Soundcloud page! You can also stream/download the album on the Shortwaves Bandcamp. Side A: Crisis (15:00) Side B: Sleeper (15:00)

name: The Disconnect [TIN015]
description: Five Star Hotel returns with their second full-length tape of the year; another slab of industrial noise, dance-floor rhythm, and harsh melodies that somehow find their way to the surface. "The Disconnect finds the Michigan producer narrowing in on what is his most focused work to date. All of the abrasiveness of Surface is expertly fused with four-to-the-floor club music to create something that is catchy and hypnotic, yet with an unexpected tinge of abusiveness." The whole album is available to stream and download on the Five Star Hotel Bandcamp. Side A: Warmth Desire N) Relief Aside Stress (~23 min.) Side B: Way Out The Disconnect (~24 min.) Artwork by Steve S. and Michael Jerome.

name: CONTEMPORARY [TIN014]
description: Released earlier in 2013 as a free download on Bandcamp, Tinnitus is proud to present for the first time physical copies of electronic/vaporwave artist General Translator's "CONTEMPORARY." From the artist: "but in strict regard to vaporware...that kind of coverage encourages people to over-intellectualize it, which in turn makes the people behind it appear unjustifiably pretentious (and in turn, completely moronic) given the type of music we specialize in. how much context can you really give to a doctored loop of a jazz instrumental? truly guys, we are sample curators at best. we put into practice the art of commodifying art...[taking] "music" and returning it to its most primordial state, "sound"." Stream a track from the album on our Soundcloud page! [side A, ~14 minutes] "Living" [side B, ~19 minutes] "Dreaming" Run is limited to 33 tapes.

name: Live Expanse 2: LIV [TINLE002]
description: This is the second volume of uninterrupted, live sessions by experimental jam collective Longitudinal Expanse. The tracks are mixed and mastered using the original multi-track recordings exclusively for this cassette release. The July 10th, 2013 sessions were selected for this release primarily because they highlight the progress made by recording and practicing nearly daily the month prior. As a result of recording dozens of hours of improvised material, the musicians were comfortable acting as a single unit and unafraid to explore the limits of their sound. "Live Expanse 2: LIV" will be released on October 29th and is limited to 15 hand-numbered copies only. The unmixed recordings are free to download and stream on the Longitudinal Expanse bandcamp, where the full liner notes can also be viewed. Charlie/Kevin - all instruments Produced by Kevin Released by TINNITUS RECORDS.

name: Surface [TIN013]
description: Blown-out harsh noise to haunt your dreams. "Surface" drowns the listener with industrial electronics while a steady, rhythmic undertone ties it all together. Stream "8FISH" on our Soundcloud! Download/stream the album from Five Star Hotel's Bandcamp! Track list: 01. Descent 02. Buzzer 03. Partial 04. 8FISH 05. Autosave 06. Crash 07. Addiction 08. Hex 09. Comedown 10. Surface Run time: 30 minutes

name: Live Expanse 1: XLVIII [TINLE001]
description: The complete recordings of improvised sessions that took place on May 24th and May 29th 2013, and the first volume of the Live Expanse series of tapes. The unmixed recordings are available to stream/download for free on Bandcamp here. The hand-numbered tape release is limited to 15 copies and is produced using the original multi-track recordings. This mix is exclusive to the cassette release. [side A - May 24th] (20:24) [side B - May 29th] (19:35) Charlie/Kevin - all instruments Produced by Kevin. Released through TINNITUS RECORDS. For complete liner notes, view this on the Longitudinal Expanse bandcamp.

name: Spirited Obstinacy [TIN012]
description: Forgotten is an Athens, Greece based metal project offering a unique sound that combines the intensity of black metal riffing with clean vocals and symphonic accompaniment. Stream "Don't Regret" on our Soundcloud! Track list: 01. Pawn 02. An Episode That's Gone 03. Silence Around 04. Don't Regret 05. Bedlam Echoes 06. Rational Self Redress All instruments & vocals - John Georgakopoulus Recorded by Nick Kritikos Mixed by Alex Bolpasis at Artracks Recording Studios Mastered by George Priniotakis at Artracks Recording Studios Cover art by Kostas Zisoulis

name: Loipe [TIN011]
description: We're proud here at Tinnitus to present the first release from German "lehmrock" band LOIPE. Combining elements of sludge, post-rock, shoegaze and math rock, this three-piece will astound you with their technical prowess and tight compositions. Stream "Biermysterium" on Soundcloud! Stream/download the EP on Bandcamp! Track list: 1. Biermysterium 2. Geilaz 3. Walter spricht 4. Echsenmensch Cassette copies available for purchase on May 31st!

name: .dll [TIN010]
description: .dll is the first release from electronic/vaporwave artist USER32. A glitchy EP inspired by the city of Tampa. "The making of this EP was inspired by the beautiful Downtown Tampa. Each track is specifically chosen to be used for this EP because of how well they capture the feelings of Downtown Tampa during daytime and during nighttime. Thank you for listening and downloading. It means a lot." Stream the title track on our Soundcloud! Stream/download the album on Bandcamp! Track list: 01. WELCOME TO 02. DOWNTOWN TAMPA 03. .dll 04. NIGHTTIME 05. IT MAKES ME WANT TO CRY Cassette run limited to 20 copies only.

name: Looking Forward as Always [808NY005]
description: From our friends at 808 New York! "Each side is a live show played in Lawrence, KS. Side one is at the Lawrence Percolator’s Pass the Hat event last month put on by Craig Comstock. The second is from the Noise Ordinance night at the 8th Street Taproom. Kind Horse offers improvisational rock and roll, heavy and dark. Iheartlocalmusic.com said their set at Percolator was “a set that was sometimes jarring, sometimes coming together harmoniously but always seemingly developing organically in the moment.” Finally something new in the Lawrence scene." Very limited number of tapes available for purchase!

name: Hologram Plaza [TIN009]
description: We're proud to present the first album from ambient/psychedelic/vaporwave project DISCONSCIOUS on cassette! Stream "Lunar Food Court" on Soundcloud! Download/stream the whole album on Bandcamp! Track list: 01. Elevator Up 02. Enter Through the Lobby 03. Mattress Store 04. Endless Escalation 05. Lunar Food Court 06. Shopping Delirium 07. Fountain Plaza 08. Absent Interlude 09. Midnight Specimen 10. Elevator Down

name: Pharmacy [TIN008]
description: Music from a void. This material was compiled with the intent of displaying our shift towards more minimal and abstract soundscapes, while not completely abandoning the rock framework present in earlier releases. All tracks are improvised and recorded live. Stream and download "Social Automaton" on Soundcloud! Watch the performance of "Rubber Riff" on YouTube! Available to stream/purchase on Bandcamp! Track list: 1. Rubber Riff 2. Falling Through 3. Subsonic Premonitions 4. Supernova 5. Approaching Absentia 6. Social Automaton 7. Wobbly Warbly Waves 8. Emptiness Produced by Kevin. Cover photo taken by Charlie. 'Rubber Riff' Recorded on 6/7/11 Charlie - bass Julian - drums Kevin - guitar 'Falling Through' Recorded on 7/13/12 Charlie - bass/keyboard Julian - drums Kevin - guitar 'Subsonic Premonitions' Recorded on 6/22/12 Charlie - bass/keyboard/drums Kevin - drums 'Supernova' Recorded during october '11 Charlie - all instruments 'Approaching Absentia' Recorded on 6/26/12 Charlie - keyboard Kevin - drums Patrick - bass 'Social Automaton' Recorded on 7/13/12 Charlie - bass Julian - drums Kevin - guitar 'Wobbly Warbly Waves' Recorded on 12/27/12 Charlie - all instruments Kevin - all instruments 'Emptiness' Recorded late August '12 Charlie - bass/drums Kevin - guitar

name: Balam [SLRT001]
description:
From our friends at Spectrelight Recordings!

From their site:
"The Hard-hitting, self-titled debut by Rhode Island’s Balam is coming to Cassette via Spectrelight Recordings. The tape contains three monster tracks of eclectic Stoner Doom, punctuated with elements of Psychedelic Rock and Shoegaze. For fans of Pilgrim, Pentagram and Sleep!"

We have a VERY limited number of tapes available to sell. So buy them soon while you can ;)

Tapes are pro-manufactured.

Track list:

01. The Followed
02. Soul Scour
03. Dark Door

name: Urban Explorers [TIN007]
description: Longitudinal Expanse's first release of 2013 is a three track EP that precedes a release of a new full length over the summer. While the earliest track of Urban Explorers is a heavy, psychedelic whirlwind, the latter two tracks show the group's gradual evolution into a more minimalist style. All tracks are recorded live and fully improvised. The digital version is available for free on Bandcamp and includes video of the performance of Psychedelic Subway. Track list: 1. Psychedelic Subway (recorded 6/7/11) 2. Coming Up the Street (recorded on 10/22/11) 3. Park Ave. (recorded on 01/14/13) tracks 1+2: charlie - bass julian - drums kevin - guitar produced by J. tracks 3: charlie - guitars kevin - drums produced by K.

name: Abducted by Jesus [TIN006]
description: Soon after releasing their first demo in June 2012, Northern Aggression began writing material for a full-length follow up. During the Abducted sessions the group found their sound moving in a nosier and more psychedelic direction, which they pursued for this release. Abducted is a concept album. A group of campers go on a late night hike and find themselves abducted by Jesus upon discovering an abandoned cemetery. Stream the title track on Soundcloud! Available to stream/purchase on Bandcamp! Track list: 1. In Search of... 2. Night Rituals 3. Excerpt #1 4. Abducted 5. Judgment at the Gates 6. Duel with the Devil 7. Excerpt #3 8. Invocation 9. Revelation 10. Savant of the Wasteland (Bonus track) Savant of the Wasteland is a reworked and re-recorded version of the track of the same name from last summer's demo. It is exclusive to the cassette version of the album.

name: Selected Works Vol. II [TIN005]
description: SWII compiles material from two days of sessions in the fall of 2011. All tracks are recorded live and fully improvised. All cassette copies of the album feature unique, hand-drawn artwork by one of the members of the project (run limited to 40 copies) and include a code to download the digital version of the release. Stream "Longborading" on Soundcloud! Available to stream/purchase on Bandcamp! Track list: 1. Solar Dust 2. Tomorrow 3. Reverberations 4. Longboarding Through the Bone Ridden Streets of Hell 5. A Long Comedown 6. Oscillation from Worlds Beyond 7. Only Drone Can Save Us Tracks 2 + 6: Charlie - All instruments All other tracks: Kevin - guitar/noise Charlie - bass/noise Julian - drums Mastered by Kevin Digital cover art by Charlie

name: Demo [TIN004]
description: We're proud here at Tinnitus to present Northern Aggression's first release! The trio formed in Newfoundland during May 2012, releasing this demo a short month later. The release tells a story of a man who hallucinates about the end of the world as his mind slowly unravels. Stream "She Is Purity..." on Soundcloud! Available to stream/purchase on Bandcamp! Track listing: 1. Drone Strikes and the March of Millions 2. Savant of the Wasteland 3. She Is Purity, She Is Corruption Limited to 66 hand-numbered copies on cassette. Credits: Promotheus - Guitar/Drums Buff Jacksonhead - Bass ... - Vocals

name: Dead Sun [TIN003]
description: Resonance. is a now defunct black metal group from Connecticut that released one EP, "Dead Sun." We're making this release available on a physical format for the first time using the original recordings. This reissue also includes a never before released track ("Ascent",) making this the complete recordings of the project. Stream "Ascent' on Soundcloud! Available to stream/purchase on Bandcamp! Track list: 1. Dead Sun 2. First Dream 3. Utopia 4. Ascent Line-up: Kevin - Guitar/Bass/Drum programming Patrick - Guitar/Vocals Cassette run limited to 35 hand-numbered copies.

name: Selected Works [TIN002]
description: On August 18th, 2011 the experimental jam collective Longitudinal Expanse convened for their fifteenth recorded session. This full length compiles material from that day. All tracks are recorded live and fully improvised. Stream "Descent Into Madness" on Soundcloud! Available to stream/purchase on Bandcamp! Track list: 1. Ludicrous Warp Speed 2. Descent Into Madness 3. Going Going Gone 4. You Know We're Not Alone? 5. Space Steps 6. Panicked Serenity 7. Untitled 8. First Contact Line-up: Kevin - Guitar/Keyboard Charlie - Bass/Keyboard Julian - Drums/Keyboard Mixed by Julian Cover art by Charlie Run of tapes limited to 30 copies only.

name: Majorana [TIN001]
description: Dorothea is a self-described "psychedelic drone doom duo." Over the course of a half hour the group expertly layers filthy sounding drones over a steady and forceful drum line. The project is an international collaboration spanning thousands of miles, with one member from the East Coast of the United States and the other on the West Coast of Norway. Tinnitus Records is proud to be the first label to release their music on a physical format. Available to stream/download on Bandcamp! Line-up: C.S. - Bass/Saxophone K.D. - Bass/Drums/Vocals Cassettes are hand numbered, limited to 50 copies.
